    <h1>TestOrg GitHub Security Posture Overview</h1>

    <div class="meta">
        <p><strong>Date:</strong> 2026-04-09 12:00 UTC · <strong>Run:</strong> test-run-id · <strong>Scope:</strong> 5 total · 5 non-archived · 0 archived repositories in
            <code>TestOrg</code></p>
    </div>

    <h2>Summary</h2>

    <p>This report provides an executive snapshot of how consistently core repository security controls
        are applied across 5 non-archived repositories in <code>TestOrg</code>
        GitHub organization.</p>

    <h3>Observability Metrics</h3>

    <p class="question">Do we communicate to external parties how to inform us about security issues found in our public
        repositories?</p>
    <p><code>Security Policy Coverage</code>: <span class="metric">66.7% (2/3)</span>
        <em>(public repos only, including archived)</em> ·
        <a href="OPERATIONS.html#security-policy-coverage" title="What it means and how to add a security policy">Read more</a>
    </p>

    <p class="question">Do we have Dependabot security updates enabled so GitHub can automatically open remediation pull
        requests for vulnerable dependencies?</p>
    <p><code>Dependabot Status</code>: <span class="metric">60.0% (3/5)</span> ·
        <a href="OPERATIONS.html#dependabot-coverage" title="What it means and how to enable Dependabot security updates">Read more</a>
    </p>

    <p class="question">Do we scan our repositories for leaked secrets?</p>
    <p><code>Secret Scanning Coverage</code>: <span class="metric">80.0% (4/5)</span> ·
        <a href="OPERATIONS.html#secret-scanning-coverage" title="What it means and how to enable secret scanning">Read more</a>
    </p>

    <h3>Ownership Metrics</h3>

    <p class="question">Do we enforce branch protection rules?</p>
    <p><code>Branch Protection</code>: <span class="metric">60.0% (3/5)</span> ·
        <a href="OPERATIONS.html#branch-protection-coverage" title="What it means and how to configure branch protection">Read more</a>
    </p>

    <p class="question">Do we have CODEOWNERS files in <code>.github/CODEOWNERS</code> or
        <code>./CODEOWNERS</code>?</p>
    <p><code>CODEOWNERS Coverage</code>: <span class="metric">80.0% (4/5)</span> ·
        <a href="OPERATIONS.html#codeowners-coverage" title="What it means, team-over-user preference, and how to add a team member">Read more</a>
    </p>

