    <p class="caveat" id="add-a-team-member">Prefer a GitHub <strong>team</strong> (for example <code>@TestOrg/team-slug</code>) as
        CODEOWNERS owner rather than an individual user: the CODEOWNERS Summary "top security teams" ranking only
        considers team-type owners, and a team survives one person leaving. To add a member to a team, contact your GitHub organization&#39;s administrators with the person&#39;s GitHub username and the team they should join — team membership is typically governed by an identity provider or admin process outside this repository, not a configuration file.</p>
    

    <h2 id="metric-caveats">Metric Caveats</h2>

    <div class="caveat">
        <p>Branch protection coverage counts only <code>pass</code> as sufficient; <code>partial</code> remains
            insufficient.</p>
    </div>

